<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,1132,1877]" box="[199,835,1527,1552]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1527,1552]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Description.</emphasis>
The following description is given by Dall:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,1132,1877]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
&quot;A still paler form [than 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1884" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1884" box="[502,844,1564,1589]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thea">
<emphasis box="[502,687,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Cerodrillia thea</emphasis>
(Dall, 
<number box="[776,835,1564,1589]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="1884.0">1884</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
] without any band was dredged by the 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1375,1564,1588]" name="United States of America" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">U.S.</collectingCountry>
Fish Commission in 
<number box="[328,368,1600,1624]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="111.0">111</number>
fms, in the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[588,676,1599,1624]" name="Mexico" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, at Station 
<number box="[800,860,1600,1624]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="2402.0">2402</number>
. In this specimen the nucleus was of a lovely bright carmine color. This form, which is probably peculiar to deep water, may take the varietal name of 
<taxonomicName box="[1243,1361,1637,1660]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carminura">
<emphasis box="[1243,1361,1637,1660]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">carminura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has seven whorls beside the nucleus, of a lemonade color, with nine ribs on the penultimate whorl, rather straighter than in the 
<typeStatus box="[276,324,1709,1732]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
[of 
<taxonomicName box="[371,452,1708,1733]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thea">
<emphasis box="[371,452,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">C. thea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] and less swollen on the periphery.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,1132,1877]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,495,1743,1768]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Remarks. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[322,495,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Nomenclature.</emphasis>
</emphasis>
This species was described without illustration as a deep-water form of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1884" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1884" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Cerodrillia thea</emphasis>
(Dall, 
<number box="[287,346,1780,1805]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="1884.0">1884</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, being paler, slimmer, of a lemonade color and having a carmine-colored protoconch (Dall, 
<number box="[151,211,1816,1840]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="1889.0">1889</number>
a: 
<number box="[237,267,1815,1840]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" value="91.0">91</number>
). The specimen illustrated by Williams has not been examined for its possible agreement with Dall’s description and as such is a candidate 
<typeStatus box="[578,670,1853,1876]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
